The financial factors can be evaluated from two different perspectives: if the surplus is sold to the grid and, therefore, there is a benefit for the investor, and if there is no sale to the grid. In the first case, consider the selling price to the grid of the surplus energy to be the value of its purchase price. To get the parameters referred, the first step is to calculate the annual cash flows, whose parameters are shown in Table 1, in which the considered tariff is the simple one. Consider year 0 to be the year in which the initial investment is made and in which the photovoltaic installation is carried out, so there is no production in that year. The data presented in Table 2 correspond to the values used in the computation of the initial investment.Table 1
