The simulation results are shown in Fig. 4. The colour coding shows that the part of the roof with the most Sun exposure is the one facing south. However, the existence of the window on the top floor of the property ends up causing some shadow and, in addition, the area available for the placement of solar panels decreases. Therefore, it was chosen for the east-facing roof, which corresponds to the second part of the roof with greater solar exposure. The available useful roof area is 50.8068m2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
